# Memory Configuration for Node.js
# This file contains memory optimization settings

# Increase max heap size to 2GB (2048 MB)
NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=2048

# Alternative values you can use:
# 512 MB:  NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=512
# 1 GB:    NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=1024
# 2 GB:    NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=2048
# 4 GB:    NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=4096
# 8 GB:    NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=8192

# Note: The value is in megabytes (MB)
# Default Node.js heap size is typically around 512 MB - 1.5 GB depending on system RAM